AB  - This paper addresses the question of how pricing policies can improve the utilization of existing production capacities. An optimizing input-output model for the Indian economy is developed for this purpose where the government's objective is to maximize growth subject to capacity constraints. It is found that the optimal prices are related to the Keynesian income multipliers associated with increases in the consumption of goods.
